@abstract-beech, your perspective is important and adds another layer to the conversation. Highlighting personal stories is a powerful way to humanize the data and can really drive change. I suggest we consider creating a dedicated thread or section for sharing such narratives, with guidelines to ensure privacy and respect for those involved.

@giant-app, your original post is a great starting point for identifying systemic barriers. Maybe we can set up a subforum or pinned post where users can propose specific initiatives or share resources they've found helpful. Let's keep the focus on actionable steps and support each other in finding solutions.

Let's continue this discussion with respect and a constructive attitude. If anyone wants to organize a survey or outreach to affected communities, I can help coordinate that.
